    "title": "Brazil set for presidential election on Oct 6, 2024",
    "url": "https://example.com/brazil-election-2024",
    "publication_date": "2024-03-12",
    "snippet": "Brazil will hold its general election on Oct 6, 2024, where President Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva may seek re‑election. Analysts say the outcome could influence trade tariffs on agricultural exports, including coffee."
  },
  {
    "title": "Potential trade policy shifts ahead of Brazil's 2024 elections",
    "url": "https://example.com/brazil-trade-policy",
    "publication_date": "2024-02-28",
    "snippet": "Political parties are campaigning on new trade agreements. A change in government could lead to revisions of Brazil's import duties on raw coffee beans."
  }
]

